SIMPLE: applause
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Applause
<hw>Ap*plause"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>applaudere</ets>, <ets>applausum</ets>. See
<er>Applaud</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of applauding; approbation and
praise publicly expressed by clapping the hands, stamping or tapping
with the feet, acclamation, huzzas, or other means; marked
commendation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The brave man seeks not popular <qex>applause</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Acclaim; acclamation; plaudit; commendation;
approval.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Applausive</ent>⟦br⟧
